Core Feature Implementation in OnlineBankingSystem
1. Account Creation

Feature: Create a new bank account for a user.

Implementation:

int id = new Random().nextInt(9000) + 1000;
IAccount acc = new SavingsAccount(id, name, pass, bal);
accountMap.put(id, acc);
dao.saveAccount(acc);


Details:

Generates a unique account ID (1000â€“9999).

Creates a SavingsAccount object (polymorphism via IAccount interface).

Saves account in-memory (HashMap) and database (JDBC).

2. Login / Authentication

Feature: Login existing account with ID and password.

Implementation:

IAccount acc = accountMap.get(id);
if (!((Account) acc).checkPassword(p)) {
    System.out.println("Wrong Password");
}


Details:

Checks if account exists in in-memory map.

Validates password using checkPassword method.

If authenticated, opens account menu.

3. Balance Check

Feature: Display current account balance.

Implementation:

System.out.println("Balance: " + acc.getBalance());


Details:

Calls getBalance() from the Account class.

Real-time display of balance.

4. Deposit

Feature: Add money to the account.

Implementation:

acc.deposit(amt);
dao.updateBalance(acc);


Details:

Synchronized deposit ensures thread-safe operations.

Updates database via AccountDAO.updateBalance.

Validates amount to be greater than 0.

5. Withdraw

Feature: Withdraw money from the account.

Implementation:

acc.withdraw(amt);
dao.updateBalance(acc);


Details:

Uses SavingsAccount.withdraw() or CurrentAccount.withdraw() for polymorphic behavior.

Validates sufficient funds (with overdraft for current account).

Exception handling prevents negative balance.

6. Multithreaded Transactions

Feature: Simulate concurrent deposits and withdrawals.

Implementation:

Thread t1 = new TransactionThread(acc, 200, true);
Thread t2 = new TransactionThread(acc, 150, false);
t1.start();
t2.start();


Details:

Demonstrates multithreading & synchronization.

synchronized ensures balance consistency.

Prints transaction completion messages in real time.

7. Account Listing

Feature: List all accounts (admin/debug feature).

Implementation:

for (IAccount a : accountMap.values()) {
    System.out.printf("ID: %d | Name: %s | Balance: %.2f\n", a.getAccountId(), a.getName(), a.getBalance());
}


Details:

Uses Collections & Generics (HashMap<Integer,IAccount>).

Provides quick overview of all accounts.

8. Database Integration (JDBC)

Feature: Persist account data in MySQL database.

Implementation:

dao.saveAccount(acc);
dao.updateBalance(acc);
dao.getAllAccounts();


Details:

Uses DBConnection for database connection.

Implements CRUD operations in AccountDAO.

Ensures data consistency between memory and database.

9. Data Validation

Feature: Validate all user inputs and transactions.

Implementation:

Deposit and withdrawal amounts > 0.

Password length validated during creation.

Checks sufficient balance for withdrawal.

Invalid inputs throw exceptions and show error messages.

